The long-term SOT increasing trend at the JPC-38 core site was punctuated by up to 1.5 °C warm events at the centennial scale, while cold events dwarfed over the course of the Holocene (Fig. 3b). Most of the gradual Holocene EAP ice shelf thinning and shrinking may be explained by the long-term subsurface ocean warming inferred from the \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
